$ $ORACLE_HOME/sqlplus/admin/glogin.sql

This SQL script is the *site profile*. It is executed when → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus is → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus#sql-plus-start[started].

After executing this script, SQL*Plus might, if it finds it, also execute a so called *user profile* (→ development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus/sqlpath/login[login.sql]).

sa:
  The parent directory → Linux/fhs/u01/app/oracle/product/vv-v-v/dbhome_n/sqlplus/admin[`$ORACLE_HOME/sqlplus/admin`]
